    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe comment for `vim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable()` mentions toggling but nothing in the function actually toggles inlay hints, even the usage comments.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n--- Enable/disable/toggle inlay hints for a buffer\r\n---\r\n--- @param bufnr (integer|nil) Buffer handle, or 0 or nil for current\r\n--- @param enable (boolean|nil) true/nil to enable, false to disable\r\n--- @since 12\r\nfunction M.enable(bufnr, enable)\r\n```\r\n\r\n`vim.lsp.inlay_hint(0, nil)` used to toggle, but the new `enable()` API doesn't do that, nor is there a function for toggling.\r\n\r\nFor now, I'm using this to toggle:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal function toggle_inlay_hints()\r\n  vim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable(0, not vim.lsp.inlay_hint.is_enabled(nil))\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's simple, but I think we should have a `vim.lsp.inlay_hint.toggle()` function or at least \"toggle if `nil`\" in `enable()` for easier usage.\r\nI can make a PR for that little change, but I'd like to know if there's been discussion on why there's no longer a single function call for toggling inlay hints, and whether it's better to put toggling in its own function or just `enable()`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nUse any LSP with inlay hints (I configured with [neovim/nvim-lspconfig](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig))\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere should be a single function call for toggling inlay hints (previously `vim.lsp.inlay_hint(0, nil)`)\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1890+g1cf51a07a\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nN/A\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
